    <div class="content-title text-center">
            <h2 class="p-name mt-1"><a href="http://blog.lan/satnav-and-lights-for-the-bicycle" class="u-url">Satnav and lights for the bicycle</a></h2>
                <span class="blog-date">
    <time class="dt-published" datetime="2016-04-24T16:52:00+01:00">
        <i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> 24th Apr 2016
    </time>
</span>
        <span class="tags">
        <a class="label label-rounded label-secondary p-category" href="http://blog.lan/tag:cycling#body-wrapper">cycling</a>
    </span>
    </div>
    <div class="e-content">
        <p>QuadLock adapters are great for quickly clipping your phone in various vehicles. I've used them on the motorcycle and scooter for some time, so I decided to do the same for the bicycle. One for the phone and another for attaching a battery pack under the cross-tube, keeps the satnav running for at least a full day cycling. Also attached a Lezyne headlamp in addition to the front and rear blinkers, for those days when we stay out late. All ready for some summer cycling! </p>

<p>Lastly I fitted some Schwalbe Marathon puncture-proof tyres to the GFs bicycle, to avoid spending my summer repairing punctures (she picked up 3 on the last trip!). </p>
